<item>
            <title>[HIVE-5599] Change default logging level to INFO</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5599</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default logging level is warn:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/trunk/common/src/java/conf/hive-log4j.properties#L19&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/trunk/common/src/java/conf/hive-log4j.properties#L19&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but hive logs lot&apos;s of good information at INFO level. Additionally most hadoop projects log at INFO by default. Let&apos;s change the logging level to INFO by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
